 def : Daemon threads which will runs in the background of another Thread
 Uses: it provides the service to the Thread
 ex : Garbage collector,AttachListeners,finalize,Spelling checker etc..
 Methods:
 public final void setDaemon(boolean b)
 public final boolean isDaemon()

 Life:its depends on the dead thread
 daemon nature:it inherits the nature/properties from its parent thread
 jvm role: JVM Behavior
           The JVM keeps running as long as at least one user thread is alive.
           When all user threads finish, the JVM terminates immediately.
           Any daemon threads that are still running are stopped automatically by the JVM.
           The JVM does not wait for daemon threads to complete their execution.
What Happens?
          1. main() creates a thread.
          2.setDaemon(true) makes it a daemon thread.
          3.main thread finishes.
           4.No user threads remain.
           5.JVM terminates.
           6.Daemon thread is stopped automatically.
 class Test extends Thread{
 Public void run(){
 System.out.println("Child thread");
 }
 public static void main(String args[]){
 System.out.println("Main Thread");

 Test t=new Test();
 t.setDaemon(true);
 t.start()
 }
 }


